ful and considered choices must be made  The Collection Review Committee of Preston Library is responsible for the selection of serial titles  The Committee meets on an ad hoc basis to review requests for serial titles and requests for other materials  Criteria for selection will include the following  The title must support the curricula of the Institute  The reputation of the title and its publisher must be sound  The subscription cost must be justifiable  The title must be indexed in abstracts and or indexes held or accessible to the Institute  Other factors to be considered include  How frequently is the title likely to be used at the Institute  How many requestors have endorsed the selection of the title  How well does the existing serial collection at the Institute cover the subject  How frequently has the title been requested via interlibrary loan  What is the frequency with which the title is cited in the professional literature  Procedures for Selection of Serial Titles The requestor fills out the Serials Subscription Request Form and returns it to the library  The library completes the form  The form is sent to the Department Head of the requesting department for approval  The form is returned to the library  The Collection Review Committee considers the request  The Department Head is notified of the decision regarding the request  If approved by the Committee  the Head of Technical Services will initiate procedures to begin a subscription to the title  Typically  subscriptions will commence with the first issue of the next calendar year or the first issue of the upcoming volume  Please return completed form to the Head of Technical Services  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Preston Library Serials Selection Criteria  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu Library Home Find Books Find Articles Get Help Services Departments About Preston Library Preston Library Staff Erika Brooke Administrative Assistant Ph   540  464 7228 Fax   540  464 7279 Preston Library Virginia Military Institute 345 Letcher Avenue Lexington  VA 24450 Contact Preston Library  Appendix B Serials Selection Criteria   The acquisition of serials requires a higher degree of selectivity than that required for monographs